      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Papers of George Frederick Wells include diaries, 1905-1958; writings on the rural
            church and various theological questions; sermons; scrapbooks and notebooks; and
            pamphlets, tracts and church programs. Also, correspondence, 1900-1958, much of it
            with World War II servicemen, but also concerning the Country Church Movement.</p>
      </scopecontent>
